6 Section 2. Section 39-11-404, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "39-11-404. (Temporary) Employer job growth incentive tax credit -- administration. (1) An
8 employer that hires qualifying new employees is eligible for an annual job growth incentive tax credit against
9 income taxes imposed pursuant to Title 15, chapter 30 or 31.
10 (2) The amount and duration of the credit is administered by the department of revenue as
11 provided in 15-30-2361 and 15-31-175.
12 (3) A qualifying employer seeking approval to claim a credit shall apply for a credit certificate with
13 the department for the preceding calendar year. The application must be submitted on a form prescribed by the
14 department on which the employer:
15 (a) identifies and describes the number of qualifying new employees hired;
16 (b) provides necessary details to calculate the net employee growth and qualifying net employee
17 growth;
18 (c) provides documentation necessary to calculate the job growth incentive tax credit, including but
19 not limited to the average yearly wage of each qualifying new employee; and
20 (d) submits any other information the department considers necessary for auditing purposes and to
21 determine whether the employer qualifies for a credit certificate.
22 (4) After receiving an application, the department shall:
23 (a) provide the employer with a credit certificate, which must accompany the employer's tax return
24 that is filed with the department of revenue; or
25 (b) deny an application for a credit certificate and provide the employer with the reasoning for the
26 denial. Prior to issuing a denial, the department shall provide the employer with an opportunity to resolve
27 deficiencies in the application.
